The paper analyzes the tweeting behavior of astrophysicists and compares it with their publication behavior and citation impact. The study involves the use of Web of Science and focuses on the impact of tweets on research-related topics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely categories include cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
